  "general": {
    "name": "payne4GAIN_modelSpectra",
    "short": "the payne4GAIN model spectra used to generate the lte, nlte, and corrected abundances in this VAC",
    "description": "We trained Payne models on grids of Turbospectrum_NLTE synthetic spectra: one in LTE and one in NLTE, using departure coefficient grids calculated in MULTI. These are the model spectra that come from our Paynes, after chi-squared fitting the APOGEE DR19 spectra that fall within our training range (according to ASPCAP). In addition to the 15-label Payne, we also fit each spectrum with 9 continuum parameters (2nd order Chebyshev polynomials for each chip), radial velocity and gaussian broadening.",
